<p><cs><col><b>Glutamic acid</b></col>, <cd>a nitrogenous organic acid
obtained from certain albuminoids, as gluten; -- called also
<altname>amido-glutaric acid</altname>.</cd></cs><-- one of the natural
L-alpha-amino acids found in many proteins <chform>C5H9NO4</chform>.
-->⟦br⟧
